Test_7

Ques1)write a program to determine if a given number is positive, negative or zero 

Ans)
function checkNumber(num) {
    if (num > 0) {
        console.log(num + " is a positive number.");
    } else if (num < 0) {
        console.log(num + " is a negative number.");
    } else {
        console.log(num + " is zero.");
    }
}

// Test the function
checkNumber(10);  // Output: 10 is a positive number.
checkNumber(-5);  // Output: -5 is a negative number.
checkNumber(0);   // Output: 0 is zero.


Ques2)write a program using prompt to input a number (1-7). use a switch statement to print the corresponding day or 'INVALID DAY' for numbers outside this range

Ans)
// Prompt the user to input a number
let num = parseInt(prompt("Enter a number between 1 and 7:"));

// Determine the corresponding day using a switch statement
switch (num) {
    case 1:
        console.log("Sunday");
        break;
    case 2:
        console.log("Monday");
        break;
    case 3:
        console.log("Tuesday");
        break;
    case 4:
        console.log("Wednesday");
        break;
    case 5:
        console.log("Thursday");
        break;
    case 6:
        console.log("Friday");
        break;
    case 7:
        console.log("Saturday");
        break;
    default:
        console.log("INVALID DAY");
}


Ques3)write a program that determines whether a person is eligible to vote based on their age(voting age is 18 or older). using ternary operator

Ans)
// Prompt the user to enter their age
let age = parseInt(prompt("Enter your age:"));

// Determine eligibility to vote using the ternary operator
let eligibility = (age >= 18) ? "You are eligible to vote." : "You are not eligible to vote.";

// Display the result
console.log(eligibility);

Ques4)write a program to print number 1 to 10 using for loop
Ans)
// Loop from 1 to 10
for (let i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
    console.log(i);
}

